<title>ITALY: Isco upbeat on Italy orders, sales in next quarter.</title>
<headline>Isco upbeat on Italy orders, sales in next quarter.</headline>
<dateline>ROME 1997-06-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Italian national economic research body Isco said on Friday that the outlook for company orders and sales in the next quarter was positive.</p>
<p>&quot;The tone of company expectations continues to indicate an upward trend,&quot; Isco said in a report on the outlook for June to September.</p>
<p>It said the investment goods sector was particularly positive. Companies' expections of economic performance in the short term also showed a fall in pessimism, Isco said.</p>
<p>-- Rome newsroom +396 678 2501</p>
